# Security & Secrets Rules

## Non-negotiable invariants (D-17 to D-19)

### D-17 — No hardcoded credentials
- **Never** write literals of keys, tokens, passwords
- **Never** `os.environ["API_KEY"]` in production code — use `common_utils.secrets.get_secret`
- **Never** commit `.env`, `.env.local`, `terraform.tfstate`, or match `.gitleaks.toml` patterns

### D-18 — Cloud-native credential delegation
- **AWS**: IRSA only — no `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID` in code or env
- **GCP**: Workload Identity only — no JSON service-account keys
- Static creds are acceptable ONLY in `.env.local` (never committed)

### D-19 — Supply chain verification before prod
- Images must be signed (Cosign keyless, GitHub OIDC)
- Images must have CycloneDX SBOM attestation (Syft)
- Kyverno admission controller rejects unsigned images in `environment=production`
- In staging/prod, image refs must be digest-pinned (`@sha256:...`) — never tag-only

## Before any commit (automatic)
```bash
gitleaks detect --no-git --source=. --redact
grep -rEI "AKIA[0-9A-Z]{16}|AIza[0-9A-Za-z_-]{35}|ghp_[A-Za-z0-9]{36}" --include="*.py" --include="*.yaml"
grep -E "os\.environ\[.(API_KEY|SECRET|TOKEN|PASSWORD)" --include="*.py"
```
Any hit → halt, chain to `/secret-breach`.

## Environment separation
| Env | Secret store | Delivery |
|-----|-------------|----------|
| Local | `.env.local` (gitignored) | dotenv |
| CI | GitHub Secrets | workflow env |
| Staging | AWS Secrets Manager / GCP Secret Manager | IRSA/WI + CSI driver |
| Production | AWS Secrets Manager / GCP Secret Manager | IRSA/WI + CSI driver (required) |

## Secret rotation is STOP-class
Never rotate silently. Always audit trail. Use `/secret-breach` workflow.

## NOT covered here (deferred by ADR-001)
- HashiCorp Vault, SLSA L3+ hermetic builds, SOC2/HIPAA compliance programs

